headline: Consumers Energy Introduces Public Safety Power Shut Off Policy to Safeguard Communities
summary: In an effort to strengthen community safety, Consumers Energy announced the launch of its Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS) policy, a proactive measure designed to reduce the continued spread of wildfires and protect communities during periods of extreme weather or other public safety threats.
